label: I am writing today as your constituent to urge you to protect key climate provisions of the reconciliation agreement. You currently have a unique and all-too-rare moment to take bold action on climate to prioritize your constituents, and allocate robust funding to protect our future, our children, and our grandchildren now and in decades to come. America has overcome famine, depression, and wars. We can marshal our resources and tackle this challenge too. Shifting to clean energy while protecting our communities from climate impacts—especially those communities disproportionately affected such as low-income communities and communities of color—presents an incredible economic opportunity for the United States. We should be cornering the market on groundbreaking technology and investments. We are living in a climate crisis and there is no time to waste. Please ensure that the reconciliation package expenditure remains as ambitious as possible to allow for critical investments, including in: - Environmental justice & a just transition: Ensure that 40 percent or more of the benefits of relevant federal legislation be invested in frontline communities—including low-income households, tribal communities, communities of color, and coal-dependent communities—as well as adequate investments in a fair transition to a clean energy economy for fossil fuel workers and communities. - Clean energy: Extend clean energy tax incentives to help ensure that 80 percent of the electricity that’s produced in the United States by 2030 comes from clean sources. - Climate resilience: Invest in programs, including the Civilian Climate Corps, to help prepare and protect communities dealing with the impacts of climate change. - Clean transportation: Electrify our transportation sector by updating the tax credit for plug-in electric vehicles or creating a point-of-sale rebate, creating a new purchase incentive for zero-emission trucks, extending the tax credit for alternative fuel infrastructure, and investing in domestic manufacturing of electric vehicles. -Resilient agriculture: Build an equitable and climate-resilient food and farm system by expanding and strengthening working lands conservation programs, re-prioritizing the US Department of Agriculture's research to incorporate and invest in climate-focused research, and strengthening support for historically marginalized farmers.Personalize your message

acts.what: 3 packages and 16 custom tests, with duplication discounts

rules.axe: multiply minor by 2, moderate by 3, serious by 4, critical by 5; sum; subtract discounts
rules.bulk: subtract 250 from visible elements; make 0 if negative; raise to 0.9th power; multiply by 0.15
rules.embAc: multiply link- or button-contained links, buttons, inputs, and selects by 5
rules.focAll: multiply discrepancy between focusable and focused element counts by 3
rules.focOp: multiply nonfocusable operable elements by 4, nonoperable focusable by 1; sum
rules.hover: multiply elements changing page on hover by 4, made visible by 2, with directly changed opacity by 0.1, with indirectly changed opacity by 0.2, unhoverable by 2; sum
rules.ibm: multiply violations by 4, recommendatons by 2; sum; subtract discounts
rules.labClash: multiply conflictually labeled elements by 2, unlabeled elements by 2; sum
rules.log: multiply log items by respective logWeights; sum
rules.menuNav: multiply Home and End errors by 1 and other key-navigation errors by 3; sum
rules.motion: get PNG screenshot sizes (sss); get differing-pixel counts between adjacent PNG screenshots (pd); “sssd” = sss difference ÷ smaller sss; multiply mean adjacent sssd, maximum adjacent sssd, maximum over-all ssd by 15; divide mean pd, maximum pd by 25,000; multiply count of non-0 pd by 10; sum
rules.radioSet: multiply radio buttons not in fieldsets with legends and no other-name radio buttons by 2
rules.role: multiple role attributes with invalid or native-HTML-equivalent values by 2
rules.styleDiff: for each of element classes block a, inline a, button, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, and h6, get diffStyles-distinct styles; multiply their count minus 1 by 2; multiply count of elements with non-plurality styles by 0.2; sum
rules.tabNav: multiply Home and End errors by 1 and other key-navigation errors by 3; sum
rules.wave: multiply alerts by 2, contrast errors by 3, errors by 4; sum; subtract discounts
